      "flags": {},
      "order": 0,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "FLUX2 native face reference inpaint.\n\nDetection only decides WHERE:\nLoad original image -> YOLO face bbox -> SAM refined face mask -> dilate/blur so cheeks, jaw, chin, and face width can change.\n\nFLUX2 decides WHAT:\nOriginal image latent + face mask -> SetLatentNoiseMask -> SamplerCustomAdvanced.\nPrompt + original image reference + up to 3 face reference images -> ReferenceLatent chain -> FluxKontextMultiReferenceLatentMethod -> FluxGuidance.\n\nUse face/head-focused references. Keep denoise low/medium for subtle detail correction; raise it if face width/fullness must move more. If using fewer than 3 face refs, bypass extra ReferenceLatent nodes or point them at the strongest reference image."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    }
